 stupid wolf. The damn thing was like a cow, so stupid it will not excape under the old fence without a will, it just munches on the grass until it is slaughtered. The dog would surely see his death if he messed with the already maddened necromancer. Did it care? probally not.. It howled then charged at Puzuzu's feet.. Grabbing on to her grey robe and pulling her down. It attempted to atleast. Puzuzu started to try and kick it in the neck.. finaly after many failed tries she succeeded kicking it right in the middle of the neck. Hoping she made it feel it the dog seemed to quit gnarling at her and sat down.. It started whining in utter pain. Puzuzu kicked it hard in the stomach killing it. It gave one last whine before dieing. <br>
<br>
Not looking back at the black wolf Puzuzu turned the corner to her underground house. Opening the door with the Innoruuk symbol on it, she spat at it, and walked down the stairs that lead to the floor of the house. Her mother was washing some robes and her father seemed to be deep in meditation. Puzuzu groaned loudly enough to get her mother's attention, &quot;What is wrong dear?&quot; The necromancer sat down pityfully like usuall, &quot;You will get your dinner, just be patient.&quot; her mother scoffed at her while trying to speed up. &quot;It's not that..&quot; Puzuzu muttered to herself, &quot;I am Innoruuk's little 4000th year sacrafice.. thats all.&quot; The pot dropped out of &quot;mom's&quot; hand... it interupted her father who had a growl on his face. &quot;YOU WHAT?&quot; Her mother screeched.. Puzuzu rolled her eyes, &quot;I am the god damn chosen one to be sacraficed to Innoruuk, ok? As in 4000th year chosen one?&quot; Her father's expression changed quickly from a maddened face to a awed glare... &quot;MY Puzuzu?... Our daughter?&quot;<br>
<br>
~Bleh.~ Puzuzu thought to herself. ~Just as I thought.~<br>
<br>
Her father put his arm around her and sat down... &quot;Our family? Our daughter?.. &quot; The mother had tears in her eyes... Puzuzu DID NOT want this type of attention at all.. here they were, proud of her when usually they were very ashamed. Always mocking her, whipping her and the such. But today they were pretty much worshiping her, muttering to themselves about how important it was, they couldn't get over it. &quot;Guys, chill out!&quot; She yelled... &quot;CHILL OUT?&quot; Her father laughed slamming his fist on the table, &quot;Out of all honor, I have finally got what I have deserved... What I have owed to Innoruuk...&quot; Puzuzu was confused, &quot;But I thought you hated Innoruuk?&quot; He shook his head, &quot;No. Not until I have realized how amazing he actually is, ok?&quot; Puzuzu gave a pouty face, &quot;I will not die for this bastard.&quot; It made her parents immediatly back up.. they had blank stares..<br>
<br>
Puzuzu didn't care. She thought they would help. But no. The odds went aggainst the favored... She kicked the door open and walked out... seeing the same black wolf once again on the ground motionless. Soon her body would be like that, stupid, non-aware, motionless... NO! She couldn't. What about her dreams of becoming a warlock?.. &quot;I will succeed in what I have been wanting for the past 4 years.&quot; She said sternly to herself. How would she bribe these people? How could she change their minds?.. She had to do something that would amaze them..<br>
<br>
